{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NvseCqrkfZBtJKbcdz9Cv1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# allocate\n2\t\n3\t`allocate.split_amount(total, parts)` splits a whole number `total` into `parts`\n4\tinteger shares.\n5\t\n6\tContract:\n7\t\n8\t- `parts` is an integer >= 1 and `total` is an integer >= 0.\n9\t- Return a list of exactly `parts` non-negative integers whose sum is exactly `total`.\n10\t- The shares are as equal as possible: every share is either `total // parts` or one\n11\t  greater, and the `total % parts` extra units go to the earliest shares, so the list\n12\t  comes out non-increasing.\n13\t\n14\tExamples:\n15\t\n16\t    split_amount(100, 3) -> [34, 33, 33]\n17\t    split_amount(90, 3)  -> [30, 30, 30]\n18\t    split_amount(7, 2)   -> [4, 3]\n19\t\n20\tRun the tests with:\n21\t\n22\t    python -m unittest discover -s tests -t .\n23\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84c6f286-fa92-4c58-a647-4f51a8d1dd68","uuid":"784018c7-241e-41ee-a364-8134ea06fc7d","timestamp":"2026-07-24T01:47:16.661Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"README.md","content":"# allocate\n\n`allocate.split_amount(total, parts)` splits a whole number `total` into `parts`\ninteger shares.\n\nContract:\n\n- `parts` is an integer >= 1 and `total` is an integer >= 0.\n- Return a list of exactly `parts` non-negative integers whose sum is exactly `total`.\n- The shares are as equal as possible: every share is either `total // parts` or one\n  greater, and the `total % parts` extra units go to the earliest shares, so the list\n  comes out non-increasing.\n\nExamples:\n\n    split_amount(100, 3) -> [34, 33, 33]\n    split_amount(90, 3)  -> [30, 30, 30]\n    split_amount(7, 2)   -> [4, 3]\n\nRun the tests with:\n\n    python -m unittest discover -s tests -t .\n","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BhfDo5ED66eXkAo7y2hNGo","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Even integer allocation for the allocate package.\n2\t\n3\tSee the package README for the full contract that ``split_amount`` is meant to\n4\tsatisfy.\n5\t\"\"\"\n6\t\n7\t\n8\tdef split_amount(total, parts):\n9\t    \"\"\"Split integer ``total`` into ``parts`` shares that are as equal as possible.\n10\t\n11\t    ``parts`` must be an integer >= 1 and ``total`` an integer >= 0. Returns a list of\n12\t    ``parts`` non-negative integers.\n13\t    \"\"\"\n14\t    if not isinstance(total, int) or not isinstance(parts, int):\n15\t        raise TypeError(\"total and parts must be integers\")\n16\t    if parts < 1:\n17\t        raise ValueError(\"parts must be at least 1\")\n18\t    if total < 0:\n19\t        raise ValueError(\"total must not be negative\")\n20\t    share = total // parts\n21\t    return [share] * parts\n22\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84c6f286-fa92-4c58-a647-4f51a8d1dd68","uuid":"1e5e6503-cd8e-4c00-897d-e77f985fe510","timestamp":"2026-07-24T01:47:16.662Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"allocate\\split.py","content":"\"\"\"Even integer allocation for the allocate package.\n\nSee the package README for the full contract that ``split_amount`` is meant to\nsatisfy.\n\"\"\"\n\n\ndef split_amount(total, parts):\n    \"\"\"Split integer ``total`` into ``parts`` shares that are as equal as possible.\n\n    ``parts`` must be an integer >= 1 and ``total`` an integer >= 0. Returns a list of\n    ``parts`` non-negative integers.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not isinstance(total, int) or not isinstance(parts, int):\n        raise TypeError(\"total and parts must be integers\")\n    if parts < 1:\n        raise ValueError(\"parts must be at least 1\")\n    if total < 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"total must not be negative\")\n    share = total // parts\n    return [share] * parts\n","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
